                            <comment id="15194417" author="sershe" created="Mon, 14 Mar 2016 23:55:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually I just realized it&apos;s a dup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-13185&quot; title=&quot;orc.ReaderImp.ensureOrcFooter() method fails on small text files with IndexOutOfBoundsException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-13185&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-13185&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15533921" author="prasanth_j" created="Thu, 29 Sep 2016 20:11:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This could still be a problem if Reader api is directly used. Hive filters 0 length files in OrcInputFormat during split generation and validateInput but if someone uses Reader api directly this could still be an issue. Ideally this should be fixed in ORC project. I will keep this open anyways for tracking. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
